{
  "comment_text": {
    "snp1.9:6.4": "Norman has “untruth”, Bodhi “destructive”. Neither notices <i lang='pi' translate='no'>vebhūtiyaṁ</i> at  <a href='https://suttacentral.net/dn30/en/sujato#2.21.2'>DN 30:2.21.2</a> and <a href='https://suttacentral.net/dn28/en/sujato#11.2'>DN 28:11.2</a>, where “divisive” fits all cases. ",
    "snp1.9:7.5": "Following the sense at <a href='https://suttacentral.net/mn99/en/sujato#13.7'>MN 99:13.7</a>, where <i lang='pi' translate='no'>mantā</i> must mean “after thought”. ",
    "snp1.9:12.4": "Read <i lang='pi' translate='no'>pasaṁsasi</i> per PTS. "
  },
