  "root_text": {
    "snp1.9:0.1": "Sutta Nipāta 1.9 ",
    "snp1.9:0.2": "Hemavatasutta ",
    "snp1.9:1.1": "“Ajja pannaraso uposatho, ",
    "snp1.9:1.2": "(iti sātāgiro yakkho) ",
    "snp1.9:1.3": "Dibbā ratti upaṭṭhitā; ",
    "snp1.9:1.4": "Anomanāmaṁ satthāraṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:1.5": "Handa passāma gotamaṁ”. ",
    "snp1.9:2.1": "“Kacci mano supaṇihito, ",
    "snp1.9:2.2": "(iti hemavato yakkho) ",
    "snp1.9:2.3": "Sabbabhūtesu tādino; ",
    "snp1.9:2.4": "Kacci iṭṭhe aniṭṭhe ca, ",
    "snp1.9:2.5": "Saṅkappassa vasīkatā”. ",
    "snp1.9:3.1": "“Mano cassa supaṇihito, ",
    "snp1.9:3.2": "(iti sātāgiro yakkho) ",
    "snp1.9:3.3": "Sabbabhūtesu tādino; ",
    "snp1.9:3.4": "Atho iṭṭhe aniṭṭhe ca, ",
    "snp1.9:3.5": "Saṅkappassa vasīkatā”. ",
    "snp1.9:4.1": "“Kacci adinnaṁ nādiyati, ",
    "snp1.9:4.2": "(iti hemavato yakkho) ",
    "snp1.9:4.3": "Kacci pāṇesu saññato; ",
    "snp1.9:4.4": "Kacci ārā pamādamhā, ",
    "snp1.9:4.5": "Kacci jhānaṁ na riñcati”. ",
    "snp1.9:5.1": "“Na so adinnaṁ ādiyati, ",
    "snp1.9:5.2": "(iti sātāgiro yakkho) ",
    "snp1.9:5.3": "Atho pāṇesu saññato; ",
    "snp1.9:5.4": "Atho ārā pamādamhā, ",
    "snp1.9:5.5": "Buddho jhānaṁ na riñcati”. ",
    "snp1.9:6.1": "“Kacci musā na bhaṇati, ",
    "snp1.9:6.2": "(iti hemavato yakkho) ",
    "snp1.9:6.3": "Kacci na khīṇabyappatho; ",
    "snp1.9:6.4": "Kacci vebhūtiyaṁ nāha, ",
    "snp1.9:6.5": "Kacci samphaṁ na bhāsati”. ",
    "snp1.9:7.1": "“Musā ca so na bhaṇati, ",
    "snp1.9:7.2": "(iti sātāgiro yakkho) ",
    "snp1.9:7.3": "Atho na khīṇabyappatho; ",
    "snp1.9:7.4": "Atho vebhūtiyaṁ nāha, ",
    "snp1.9:7.5": "Mantā atthañca bhāsati”. ",
    "snp1.9:8.1": "“Kacci na rajjati kāmesu, ",
    "snp1.9:8.2": "(iti hemavato yakkho) ",
    "snp1.9:8.3": "Kacci cittaṁ anāvilaṁ; ",
    "snp1.9:8.4": "Kacci mohaṁ atikkanto, ",
    "snp1.9:8.5": "Kacci dhammesu cakkhumā”. ",
    "snp1.9:9.1": "“Na so rajjati kāmesu, ",
    "snp1.9:9.2": "(iti sātāgiro yakkho) ",
    "snp1.9:9.3": "Atho cittaṁ anāvilaṁ; ",
    "snp1.9:9.4": "Sabbamohaṁ atikkanto, ",
    "snp1.9:9.5": "Buddho dhammesu cakkhumā”. ",
    "snp1.9:10.1": "“Kacci vijjāya sampanno, ",
    "snp1.9:10.2": "(iti hemavato yakkho) ",
    "snp1.9:10.3": "Kacci saṁsuddhacāraṇo; ",
    "snp1.9:10.4": "Kaccissa āsavā khīṇā, ",
    "snp1.9:10.5": "Kacci natthi punabbhavo”. ",
    "snp1.9:11.1": "“Vijjāya ceva sampanno, ",
    "snp1.9:11.2": "(iti sātāgiro yakkho) ",
    "snp1.9:11.3": "Atho saṁsuddhacāraṇo; ",
    "snp1.9:11.4": "Sabbassa āsavā khīṇā, ",
    "snp1.9:11.5": "Natthi tassa punabbhavo”. ",
    "snp1.9:12.1": "“Sampannaṁ munino cittaṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:12.2": "Kammunā byappathena ca; ",
    "snp1.9:12.3": "Vijjācaraṇasampannaṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:12.4": "Dhammato naṁ pasaṁsati”. ",
    "snp1.9:13.1": "“Sampannaṁ munino cittaṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:13.2": "Kammunā byappathena ca; ",
    "snp1.9:13.3": "Vijjācaraṇasampannaṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:13.4": "Dhammato anumodasi. ",
    "snp1.9:14.1": "Sampannaṁ munino cittaṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:14.2": "Kammunā byappathena ca; ",
    "snp1.9:14.3": "Vijjācaraṇasampannaṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:14.4": "Handa passāma gotamaṁ”. ",
    "snp1.9:15.1": "“Eṇijaṅghaṁ kisaṁ vīraṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:15.2": "Appāhāraṁ alolupaṁ; ",
    "snp1.9:15.3": "Muniṁ vanasmiṁ jhāyantaṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:15.4": "Ehi passāma gotamaṁ. ",
    "snp1.9:16.1": "Sīhaṁvekacaraṁ nāgaṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:16.2": "Kāmesu anapekkhinaṁ; ",
    "snp1.9:16.3": "Upasaṅkamma pucchāma, ",
    "snp1.9:16.4": "Maccupāsappamocanaṁ. ",
    "snp1.9:17.1": "Akkhātāraṁ pavattāraṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:17.2": "Sabbadhammāna pāraguṁ; ",
    "snp1.9:17.3": "Buddhaṁ verabhayātītaṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:17.4": "Mayaṁ pucchāma gotamaṁ”. ",
    "snp1.9:18.1": "“Kismiṁ loko samuppanno, ",
    "snp1.9:18.2": "(iti hemavato yakkho) ",
    "snp1.9:18.3": "Kismiṁ kubbati santhavaṁ; ",
    "snp1.9:18.4": "Kissa loko upādāya, ",
    "snp1.9:18.5": "Kismiṁ loko vihaññati”. ",
    "snp1.9:19.1": "“Chasu loko samuppanno, ",
    "snp1.9:19.2": "(hemavatāti bhagavā) ",
    "snp1.9:19.3": "Chasu kubbati santhavaṁ; ",
    "snp1.9:19.4": "Channameva upādāya, ",
    "snp1.9:19.5": "Chasu loko vihaññati”. ",
    "snp1.9:20.1": "“Katamaṁ taṁ upādānaṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:20.2": "Yattha loko vihaññati; ",
    "snp1.9:20.3": "Niyyānaṁ pucchito brūhi, ",
    "snp1.9:20.4": "Kathaṁ dukkhā pamuccati”. ",
    "snp1.9:21.1": "“Pañca kāmaguṇā loke, ",
    "snp1.9:21.2": "Manochaṭṭhā paveditā; ",
    "snp1.9:21.3": "Ettha chandaṁ virājetvā, ",
    "snp1.9:21.4": "Evaṁ dukkhā pamuccati. ",
    "snp1.9:22.1": "Etaṁ lokassa niyyānaṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:22.2": "Akkhātaṁ vo yathātathaṁ; ",
    "snp1.9:22.3": "Etaṁ vo ahamakkhāmi, ",
    "snp1.9:22.4": "Evaṁ dukkhā pamuccati”. ",
    "snp1.9:23.1": "“Ko sūdha tarati oghaṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:23.2": "Kodha tarati aṇṇavaṁ; ",
    "snp1.9:23.3": "Appatiṭṭhe anālambe, ",
    "snp1.9:23.4": "Ko gambhīre na sīdati”. ",
    "snp1.9:24.1": "“Sabbadā sīlasampanno, ",
    "snp1.9:24.2": "Paññavā susamāhito; ",
    "snp1.9:24.3": "Ajjhattacintī satimā, ",
    "snp1.9:24.4": "Oghaṁ tarati duttaraṁ. ",
    "snp1.9:25.1": "Virato kāmasaññāya, ",
    "snp1.9:25.2": "Sabbasaṁyojanātigo; ",
    "snp1.9:25.3": "Nandībhavaparikkhīṇo, ",
    "snp1.9:25.4": "So gambhīre na sīdati”. ",
    "snp1.9:26.1": "“Gambhīrapaññaṁ nipuṇatthadassiṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:26.2": "Akiñcanaṁ kāmabhave asattaṁ; ",
    "snp1.9:26.3": "Taṁ passatha sabbadhi vippamuttaṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:26.4": "Dibbe pathe kamamānaṁ mahesiṁ. ",
    "snp1.9:27.1": "Anomanāmaṁ nipuṇatthadassiṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:27.2": "Paññādadaṁ kāmālaye asattaṁ; ",
    "snp1.9:27.3": "Taṁ passatha sabbaviduṁ sumedhaṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:27.4": "Ariye pathe kamamānaṁ mahesiṁ. ",
    "snp1.9:28.1": "Sudiṭṭhaṁ vata no ajja, ",
    "snp1.9:28.2": "Suppabhātaṁ suhuṭṭhitaṁ; ",
    "snp1.9:28.3": "Yaṁ addasāma sambuddhaṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:28.4": "Oghatiṇṇamanāsavaṁ. ",
    "snp1.9:29.1": "Ime dasasatā yakkhā, ",
    "snp1.9:29.2": "Iddhimanto yasassino; ",
    "snp1.9:29.3": "Sabbe taṁ saraṇaṁ yanti, ",
    "snp1.9:29.4": "Tvaṁ no satthā anuttaro. ",
    "snp1.9:30.1": "Te mayaṁ vicarissāma, ",
    "snp1.9:30.2": "Gāmā gāmaṁ nagā nagaṁ; ",
    "snp1.9:30.3": "Namassamānā sambuddhaṁ, ",
    "snp1.9:30.4": "Dhammassa ca sudhammatan”ti. ",
    "snp1.9:30.5": "Hemavatasuttaṁ navamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "snp1.9:0.1": "Anthology of Discourses 1.9 ",
    "snp1.9:0.2": "With Hemavata ",
    "snp1.9:1.1": "“Today is the fifteenth day sabbath,” ",
    "snp1.9:1.2": "said Sātāgira, the native spirit of mount Sātā, ",
    "snp1.9:1.3": "“a holy night is at hand. ",
    "snp1.9:1.4": "Come now, let us see Gotama, ",
    "snp1.9:1.5": "the Teacher of peerless name.” ",
    "snp1.9:2.1": "“Isn’t his mind well-disposed,” ",
    "snp1.9:2.2": "said Hemavata, the native spirit of the Himalayas, ",
    "snp1.9:2.3": "“impartial toward all creatures? ",
    "snp1.9:2.4": "And aren’t his thoughts under control ",
    "snp1.9:2.5": "when it comes to likes and dislikes?” ",
    "snp1.9:3.1": "“His mind is well-disposed,” ",
    "snp1.9:3.2": "said Sātāgira, ",
    "snp1.9:3.3": "“impartial towards all creatures. ",
    "snp1.9:3.4": "His thoughts are under control ",
    "snp1.9:3.5": "when it comes to his likes and dislikes.” ",
    "snp1.9:4.1": "“Doesn’t he not steal?” ",
    "snp1.9:4.2": "said Hemavata, ",
    "snp1.9:4.3": "“And doesn’t he harm not a creature? ",
    "snp1.9:4.4": "Isn’t he far from negligence? ",
    "snp1.9:4.5": "And doesn’t he not neglect absorption?” ",
    "snp1.9:5.1": "“He does not take what is not given,” ",
    "snp1.9:5.2": "said Sātāgira, ",
    "snp1.9:5.3": "“and he harms not a creature. ",
    "snp1.9:5.4": "He is far from negligence—",
    "snp1.9:5.5": "the Buddha does not neglect absorption.” ",
    "snp1.9:6.1": "“Doesn’t he avoid lying?” ",
    "snp1.9:6.2": "said Hemavata, ",
    "snp1.9:6.3": "“And doesn’t he not speak sharply? ",
    "snp1.9:6.4": "Doesn’t he avoid backbiting, ",
    "snp1.9:6.5": "as well as speaking nonsense?” ",
    "snp1.9:7.1": "“He does not lie,” ",
    "snp1.9:7.2": "said Sātāgira, ",
    "snp1.9:7.3": "“nor does he speak sharply. ",
    "snp1.9:7.4": "He avoids backbiting, ",
    "snp1.9:7.5": "and thoughtfully speaks wise counsel.” ",
    "snp1.9:8.1": "“Doesn’t he find sensual pleasures unattractive?” ",
    "snp1.9:8.2": "said Hemavata, ",
    "snp1.9:8.3": "“And isn’t his mind unclouded? ",
    "snp1.9:8.4": "Hasn’t he escaped delusion? ",
    "snp1.9:8.5": "Does his eye see clearly in all things?” ",
    "snp1.9:9.1": "“He does not find sensual pleasures attractive,” ",
    "snp1.9:9.2": "said Sātāgira, ",
    "snp1.9:9.3": "“and his mind is unclouded. ",
    "snp1.9:9.4": "He has escaped all delusion—",
    "snp1.9:9.5": "the Buddha, whose eye sees clearly in all things.” ",
    "snp1.9:10.1": "“Isn’t he accomplished in knowledge?” ",
    "snp1.9:10.2": "said Hemavata, ",
    "snp1.9:10.3": "“And doesn’t he live a pure life? ",
    "snp1.9:10.4": "Aren’t his defilements all ended? ",
    "snp1.9:10.5": "Doesn’t he have no future lives?” ",
    "snp1.9:11.1": "“He is accomplished in knowledge,” ",
    "snp1.9:11.2": "said Sātāgira, ",
    "snp1.9:11.3": "“and he does live a pure life. ",
    "snp1.9:11.4": "His defilements are all ended, ",
    "snp1.9:11.5": "there’ll be no more future lives for him.” ",
    "snp1.9:12.1": "“Accomplished is the sage’s mind ",
    "snp1.9:12.2": "in action and in speech, ",
    "snp1.9:12.3": "and he’s accomplished in knowledge and conduct ",
    "snp1.9:12.4": "as per the teaching you praise.” ",
    "snp1.9:13.1": "“Accomplished is the sage’s mind ",
    "snp1.9:13.2": "in action and in speech, ",
    "snp1.9:13.3": "and he’s accomplished in knowledge and conduct ",
    "snp1.9:13.4": "as per the teaching you rejoice in. ",
    "snp1.9:14.1": "Accomplished is the sage’s mind ",
    "snp1.9:14.2": "in action and in speech, ",
    "snp1.9:14.3": "and he’s accomplished in knowledge and conduct: ",
    "snp1.9:14.4": "come now, let us see Gotama.” ",
    "snp1.9:15.1": "“The hero so lean, with antelope calves, ",
    "snp1.9:15.2": "not greedy, eating little, ",
    "snp1.9:15.3": "the sage meditating alone in the forest, ",
    "snp1.9:15.4": "come now, let us see Gotama. ",
    "snp1.9:16.1": "A giant, wandering alone like a lion, ",
    "snp1.9:16.2": "unconcerned for sensual pleasures, ",
    "snp1.9:16.3": "let’s approach him and ask about ",
    "snp1.9:16.4": "release from the snare of death.” ",
    "snp1.9:17.1": "“The communicator, the instructor, ",
    "snp1.9:17.2": "who has gone beyond all things, ",
    "snp1.9:17.3": "Awakened, beyond enmity and fear, ",
    "snp1.9:17.4": "let us ask Gotama.” ",
    "snp1.9:18.1": "“What has the world arisen in?” ",
    "snp1.9:18.2": "said Hemavata, ",
    "snp1.9:18.3": "What does it get close to? ",
    "snp1.9:18.4": "By grasping what ",
    "snp1.9:18.5": "is the world troubled in what?” ",
    "snp1.9:19.1": "“The world’s arisen in six,” ",
    "snp1.9:19.2": "said the Buddha to Hemavata. ",
    "snp1.9:19.3": "“It gets close to six. ",
    "snp1.9:19.4": "Derived from the six, ",
    "snp1.9:19.5": "the world’s troubled in six.” ",
    "snp1.9:20.1": "“What is that grasping ",
    "snp1.9:20.2": "by which the world is troubled? ",
    "snp1.9:20.3": "Tell us the exit when asked: ",
    "snp1.9:20.4": "how is one released from all suffering?” ",
    "snp1.9:21.1": "“The world has five kinds of sensual stimulation, ",
    "snp1.9:21.2": "and the mind is said to be the sixth. ",
    "snp1.9:21.3": "When you’ve discarded desire for these, ",
    "snp1.9:21.4": "you’re released from all suffering. ",
    "snp1.9:22.1": "This is the exit from the world, ",
    "snp1.9:22.2": "explained in accord with the truth. ",
    "snp1.9:22.3": "The way I’ve explained it is how ",
    "snp1.9:22.4": "you’re released from all suffering.” ",
    "snp1.9:23.1": "“Who here crosses the flood, ",
    "snp1.9:23.2": "Who crosses the deluge? ",
    "snp1.9:23.3": "Who, not standing and unsupported, ",
    "snp1.9:23.4": "does not sink in the deep?” ",
    "snp1.9:24.1": "“Someone who is always endowed with ethics, ",
    "snp1.9:24.2": "wise and serene, ",
    "snp1.9:24.3": "inwardly reflective, mindful, ",
    "snp1.9:24.4": "crosses the flood so hard to cross. ",
    "snp1.9:25.1": "Someone who desists from sensual perception, ",
    "snp1.9:25.2": "who has escaped all fetters, ",
    "snp1.9:25.3": "and has ended relish for rebirth, ",
    "snp1.9:25.4": "does not sink in the deep.” ",
    "snp1.9:26.1": "“Behold him of wisdom deep <j>who sees the subtle meaning, ",
    "snp1.9:26.2": "who has nothing, unattached to sensual life, ",
    "snp1.9:26.3": "everywhere free, ",
    "snp1.9:26.4": "the great seer treading the holy road. ",
    "snp1.9:27.1": "Behold him of peerless name <j>who sees the subtle meaning, ",
    "snp1.9:27.2": "giver of wisdom, <j>unattached to the realm of sensuality: ",
    "snp1.9:27.3": "see him, the all-knower, so very intelligent, ",
    "snp1.9:27.4": "the great seer treading the noble road.” ",
    "snp1.9:28.1": "“It was a fine sight for us today, ",
    "snp1.9:28.2": "a good dawn, a good rising, ",
    "snp1.9:28.3": "to see the Awakened One, ",
    "snp1.9:28.4": "the undefiled one who has crossed the flood. ",
    "snp1.9:29.1": "These thousand native spirits ",
    "snp1.9:29.2": "powerful and glorious, ",
    "snp1.9:29.3": "all go to you for refuge, ",
    "snp1.9:29.4": "you are our supreme Teacher. ",
    "snp1.9:30.1": "We shall journey ",
    "snp1.9:30.2": "village to village, peak to peak, ",
    "snp1.9:30.3": "paying homage to the Buddha, ",
    "snp1.9:30.4": "and the clear rightness of the teaching!” "
  },
